Fortuna, Lotos, PZU May Move: Central European Equity Preview

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   D o r o t a   B a r t y z e l
-- 
2011-08-24T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/fortuna-lotos-pzu-may-move-central-european-equity-preview.html
The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in central European
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names.
Share prices are from the last close.  Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 0.1 percent, the Czech PX Index
rose 1.6 percent and  Hungary ’s BUX Index fell 0.7 percent.  Fortuna Entertainment Group NV (FORTUNA)  : The Czech
betting company that sold shares last year will report first-
half earnings today. Fortuna rose 0.6 percent to 105.5 koruna.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  : Poland’s second-largest oil
refiner will release earnings for the second quarter today.
Lotos fell 2.9 percent to 32 zloty.  PZU SA (PZU PW): Poland’s biggest insurer will report
first-half earnings today. Its shares rose 2.1 percent to 336.5
zloty.  To contact the reporters on this story:
